## What are the cheapest Cometly alternatives?

Cometly isn't the only option for ad-spend-heavy brands. Here's how alternatives price differently:

| Platform | Pricing Model | Free Tier | Entry Paid | Best For |
|----------|--------------|-----------|------------|----------|
| **Triple Whale** | GMV-based | Yes | $129/mo | Shopify brands |
| **Northbeam** | Pageview-based | No | $999/mo | DTC ML attribution |
| **mbuzz** | Flat tiers | Yes | $29/mo | Model flexibility |
| **Hyros** | Revenue-based | No | ~$199/mo | High-ticket products |
| **GA4** | Free | Yes | N/A | Basic analytics |

*Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product. We've included it as one option among several.*

### 1. Triple Whale — Shopify All-in-One ($129-549/mo)

Triple Whale bundles attribution, AI recommendations (Moby), RFM audiences, and product analytics. GMV-based pricing. Deep Shopify integration.

**Why consider over Cometly:** More comprehensive (email/SMS, affiliate, product analytics). Free tier available. AI recommendations (Moby) are comparable to Cometly's AI Ads Manager.

**Why stick with Cometly:** Cometly's CAPI enrichment is stronger. Better for non-Shopify platforms. Works across Meta, Google, TikTok without Shopify dependency.

Read more: [Triple Whale Pricing](/articles/triple-whale-pricing)

### 2. Northbeam — ML Attribution ($999/mo)

Northbeam uses ML fractional attribution that prevents overcounting. Pageview-based pricing. Creative analytics on Professional tier.

**Why consider over Cometly:** ML prevents overcounting (sums to 100%). Creative analytics show which specific creatives drive revenue. MMM+ for budget allocation.

**Why stick with Cometly:** Cometly is cheaper at lower ad-spend levels. CAPI enrichment is unique to Cometly. AI Ads Manager provides more actionable recommendations for non-technical teams.

Read more: [Northbeam Pricing](/articles/northbeam-pricing)

### 3. mbuzz — Flat Pricing at $29-299/mo

mbuzz offers 7 attribution models with custom rules and server-side tracking. Flat tiers — price doesn't scale with ad spend. *Full disclosure: mbuzz is our product.*

| mbuzz Tier | Price | Records |
|------------|-------|---------|
| Free | $0 | <%= free_event_limit_display %> |
| Starter | $29/mo | 1M |
| Growth | $99/mo | 5M |
| Pro | $299/mo | 25M |

**Why consider over Cometly:** Transparent pricing. No ad-spend scaling. 7 attribution models vs 4. All-channel coverage (not just paid ads). Server-side tracking captures 30-40% more data. Custom attribution rules.

**Why stick with Cometly:** Cometly's CAPI enrichment is unique. AI Ads Manager provides campaign-specific recommendations. Better for pure paid-ads businesses. Pixel setup is simpler than SDK integration.

### 4. Hyros — High-Ticket Products (~$199/mo)

Hyros specializes in high-ticket and info product attribution with call tracking.

**Why consider over Cometly:** Cheaper. Better for high-ticket ($500+) products and info products. Call tracking included.

**Why stick with Cometly:** Cometly is better for standard e-commerce. CAPI enrichment improves Meta performance. Broader ad platform coverage.

### 5. GA4 — Free

Google Analytics 4 is free. Not a Cometly replacement, but a baseline.

**Why consider over Cometly:** Free. Immediate setup. Good enough for very early-stage measurement.

**Why stick with Cometly:** GA4 doesn't offer CAPI enrichment, AI recommendations, or multi-platform ad attribution.

